You just have to approach the situation differently, and be willing to look at new offers if the fee structures and payment agreements do not match your financial abilities, Green says. If you do have credit card debt, prioritize what needs to be paid first so you allocate your money efficiently. "The best routine is to pay them off every month," says Paula Heichel, vice president of investments at Wells Fargo.
